Would love to see what all the options are:

![screen shot 2016-10-27 at 1 11 44 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5479/19765115/fd3bc8d8-9c46-11e6-9b38-e11a59372e9c.png)

comment_data.body: I don't believe they show up until you hit F1.

Here's what I see when I hit F1:

![screen shot 2016-10-27 at 1 16 03 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5479/19765231/8dd777a2-9c47-11e6-9688-30ca0c2dda44.png)

Maybe analyzer/dartdoc doesn't know how to show docs per named arg?

I think Matan filed a similar issue to this.
cc @matanlurey

I volunteer the Flutter team to add the dartdocs if the IDE showed them.

cc @Hixie

This may also require dartdoc changes so that the docs appear in the documentation.

Ideally arguments of the kind this.foo would automatically defer to the foo property otherwise we're in for a staggering amount of duplication...

I updated the title. I think this is a request for:
- letting named params be dardoc'd
- having dartdoc recognize as such
- borrowing docs automatically from associated members
- have tooltips and completions show these docs
- changing the style guide to support this type of usage (currently, it specifies docing params using in-line prose in the method dartdoc)
So, when displaying the completions for the ctor param `foo`, if it's auto-assigned to the field `foo` (`this.foo`), we should display the docs for the member `foo`.
Konstantin, I'll follow up with some context.

[CL for Analysis Server](https://codereview.chromium.org/2683233002)
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/384794/22798802/3388bd1a-eeb8-11e6-89f5-683cbb750b19.png)

Awesome, thanks!
The CL [was landed](https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/663b7f665e63eb9062028022d47dd24c56b789ff). Changes to IDEA Dart plugin still should be made.
Yep, YouTrack issue is welcome.
@devoncarew to create the YouTrack entry
Created here: https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WEB-25478.
Fixed
Was this change in the IJ or the Dart plugin? Just trying to figure out when and where it will be available.
The Dart plugin, so likely available in 2017.3.
Yes, available in 2017.3 EAP + compatible Dart plugin

yay, confirmed working in 2017.3!
